About Our Client

The employer is a reputable organisation within the insurance industry, recognised for its commitment to delivering innovative solutions. Operating as part of a well-established company, the team is focused on achieving excellence in technology and data-driven decisions.

Job Description

Canonical / Logical Data Model Literacy Can read and interpret a CDM/LDM, understand entity relationships, and apply mapping principles consistently - not just map field-to-field but understand why a field belongs where it does in the canonical model.
SQL Proficiency Able to write and validate SQL queries to profile source data, test transformation logic, and verify mapped outputs.
Data Profiling & Quality Assessment Ability to interrogate source data independently - identify anomalies, and undocumented business logic embedded in data. 
Microsoft Fabric / Medallion Architecture Awareness Understanding of Bronze \u2192 Silver \u2192 Gold layering, and how mapping decisions affect downstream Silver and Gold outputs. Doesn't need to be a Fabric engineer, but must understand the architecture they're mapping into.
Insurance Domain Knowledge Familiarity with core insurance concepts essential if the person is a fast learner with strong insurance fundamentals.
Business Rules Elicitation Comfortable engaging with business SMEs to surface undocumented rules. This person can't just wait to be told - they need to ask the right questions and know when to escalate ambiguity vs. make a documented assumption.
Data Dictionary Interpretation Ability to work from imperfect or incomplete source documentation and not be paralysed by it. Given Pure's data dictionary gaps, this is non-negotiabl

