About the job
DWS are seeking a highly capable Certified Palantir Specialist who can confidently lead development work in an environment with essentially no existing Palantir expertise. 
This role suits individuals with deep Palantir Foundry knowledge, with at least one Palantir Certification and who comes from either a Palantir data engineering background or an Palantir application/dashboard development background. You will play a critical role in shaping and delivering key outcomes, bringing strong technical leadership and hands\u2011on capability.

 
 Where: Melbourne, Inner East Suburbs
 Type: ACN Contractor / Max Term
 Start: ASAP
 Length: 6+ months
 Style: Hybrid; 3+ days onsite
 Salary: by negotiation

 
 To succeed in this role, you will bring deep, professional consultant level expertise in Palantir and significant experience in one (or both) of the following capability areas:
 
 Essential Core Skills & Experience:
  At least one Palantir Certification; Palantir Data Engineer, Palantir Application Developer, or Palantir Data Analyst depending on which focuse area you have
Expert capability with Palantir Foundry, including Ontology and data modelling concepts.
Ability to provide technical leadership and operate independently in a low\u2011support environment.
Strong proficiency in SQL / Python.
Experience working with data pipelines, transformations, and integrating data for operational or analytical use.
