The opportunity

This is an exciting opportunity to play a key role in shaping how GMCT uses data to inform decisions, improve performance and better serve our communities.

As the Enterprise Data and Insights Analyst, you will design and deliver meaningful dashboards, analysis and insights that provide a clear, organisation-wide view of performance, customer trends and emerging opportunities. By bringing together data from multiple systems, you will help translate complex information into practical insights that support day-to-day operations and strategic decision-making. Working within the Governance Directorate, you will also play an important role in strengthening GMCT’s data governance and data maturity. You will help establish consistent standards, improve data quality and build confidence in how data is used across the organisation.

Beyond reporting, this role is about building capability and culture. You will support the growth of self-service business intelligence, provide training and guidance to stakeholders, and contribute to a collaborative, organisation-wide approach to data and insights. This is a great opportunity for someone who enjoys both the technical and engagement aspects of data, combining analysis, storytelling and stakeholder collaboration to drive better outcomes across the organisation.

Your responsibilities will include: 

Design, build, and maintain enterprise dashboards in Power BI that deliver clear, accurate, and timely insights, supporting data-driven decision-making across the organisation.
Continuously improve existing reporting tools and dashboards by streamlining data sources, enhancing usability, and ensuring outputs align with evolving business priorities.
Conduct in-depth data analysis and create reports on critical business topics, translating complex datasets into actionable insights that drive operational and strategic outcomes.
Expose, integrate, and enhance existing qualitative and quantitative data from CRM and other business systems to provide organisation-wide and aggregated customer insights.
Embed a structured data governance framework that minimises duplication, ensures efficient utilisation of existing data sets, and establishes clear standards for enterprise-wide data quality, security, and integrity. Be the leader in a decentralised model.
Update and maintain data governance policies and standards to manage and monitor data quality, while implementing a self-service governance model for data stewards and custodians supported by a cross-functional domain steering group.
Provide training and education across the business to build capability in self-service business intelligence tools, fostering a culture of data literacy and informed decision-making.
Establish structured processes for data source management including approval, integration, and ongoing oversight of additional data sources, ensuring consistency and alignment with enterprise standards.
Develop and manage a reporting and analysis prioritisation process to assess demand, allocate resources effectively, and balance capacity and capability in the delivery of enterprise data products.
Champion and actively contribute to a cross-functional Data and Insights Community, fostering collaboration, knowledge sharing, and consistent practices that strengthen data capability and maturity across the organisation.


